#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.72"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.72:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.72:0.2"
msgid "8. Ānandavagga"
msgstr "8. Ānanda"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.72:0.3"
msgid "72. Ājīvakasutta"
msgstr "72. A Disciple of the Ājīvakas"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā ānando kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time Venerable Ānanda was staying near Kosambi, in Ghosita’s "
"Monastery."

msgctxt "an3.72:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho aññataro ājīvakasāvako gahapati yenāyasmā ānando tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho so ājīvakasāvako gahapati āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then a householder who was a disciple of the <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetics went up "
"to Venerable Ānanda, bowed, sat down to one side, and said to Ānanda:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.218"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:2.1"
msgid "“Kesaṃ no, bhante ānanda, dhammo svākkhāto?"
msgstr "“Sir, whose teaching is well explained?"

#. VAR: suppaṭipannā → supaṭipannā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.72:2.2"
msgid "Ke loke suppaṭipannā?"
msgstr "Who in the world is practicing well?"

#. VAR: sukatā”ti → sugatāti (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.72:2.3"
msgid "Ke loke sukatā”ti?"
msgstr "Who in the world has done well?”"

msgctxt "an3.72:2.4"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, gahapati, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi, yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, householder, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can "
"answer as you like."

msgctxt "an3.72:2.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "an3.72:2.6"
msgid ""
"ye rāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, dosassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, "
"mohassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, tesaṃ dhammo svākkhāto no vā?"
msgstr ""
"Is the teaching of those who teach for giving up greed, hate, and delusion "
"well explained or not?"

msgctxt "an3.72:2.7"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

msgctxt "an3.72:2.8"
msgid ""
"“Ye, bhante, rāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, dosassa pahānāya dhammaṃ "
"desenti, mohassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, tesaṃ dhammo svākkhāto."
msgstr ""
"“The teaching of those who teach for giving up greed, hate, and delusion is "
"well explained."

msgctxt "an3.72:2.9"
msgid "Evaṃ me ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:3.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "“What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "an3.72:3.2"
msgid ""
"ye rāgassa pahānāya paṭipannā, dosassa pahānāya paṭipannā, mohassa pahānāya "
"paṭipannā, te loke suppaṭipannā no vā?"
msgstr ""
"Are those who practice for giving up greed, hate, and delusion practicing "
"well or not?"

msgctxt "an3.72:3.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

msgctxt "an3.72:3.4"
msgid ""
"“Ye, bhante, rāgassa pahānāya paṭipannā, dosassa pahānāya paṭipannā, mohassa "
"pahānāya paṭipannā, te loke suppaṭipannā."
msgstr ""
"“Those who practice for giving up greed, hate, and delusion are practicing "
"well."

msgctxt "an3.72:3.5"
msgid "Evaṃ me ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:4.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, gahapati, "
msgstr "“What do you think, householder? "

msgctxt "an3.72:4.2"
msgid ""
"yesaṃ rāgo pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ "
"anuppādadhammo, yesaṃ doso pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato "
"āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo, yesaṃ moho pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato "
"anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo, te loke sukatā no vā?"
msgstr ""
"Have those who’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion—so they’re cut off at "
"the root, made like a palm stump, obliterated, and unable to arise in the "
"future—done well in the world, or not?"

msgctxt "an3.72:4.3"
msgid "Kathaṃ vā te ettha hotī”ti?"
msgstr "Or how do you see this?”"

msgctxt "an3.72:4.4"
msgid ""
"“Yesaṃ, bhante, rāgo pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ "
"anuppādadhammo, yesaṃ doso pahīno … pe … yesaṃ moho pahīno ucchinnamūlo "
"tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṅkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo, te loke sukatā."
msgstr ""
"“Those who’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion have done well in the world."

msgctxt "an3.72:4.5"
msgid "Evaṃ me ettha hotī”ti."
msgstr "That’s how I see it.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: tayāvetaṃ → tayā cetaṃ (bj, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "an3.72:5.1"
msgid "“Iti kho, gahapati, tayāvetaṃ byākataṃ:"
msgstr "“So, householder, you’ve declared:"

msgctxt "an3.72:5.2"
msgid ""
"‘ye, bhante, rāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, dosassa pahānāya dhammaṃ "
"desenti, mohassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desenti, tesaṃ dhammo svākkhāto’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘The teaching of those who teach for giving up greed, hate, and delusion is "
"well explained.’"

msgctxt "an3.72:5.3"
msgid "Tayāvetaṃ byākataṃ:"
msgstr "And you’ve declared:"

msgctxt "an3.72:5.4"
msgid ""
"‘ye, bhante, rāgassa pahānāya paṭipannā, dosassa pahānāya paṭipannā, mohassa "
"pahānāya paṭipannā, te loke suppaṭipannā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those who practice for giving up greed, hate, and delusion are practicing "
"well.’"

msgctxt "an3.72:5.5"
msgid "Tayāvetaṃ byākataṃ:"
msgstr "And you’ve declared:"

msgctxt "an3.72:5.6"
msgid ""
"‘yesaṃ, bhante, rāgo pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ "
"anuppādadhammo, yesaṃ doso pahīno … pe … yesaṃ moho pahīno ucchinnamūlo "
"tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo, te loke sukatā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Those who’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion have done well in the "
"world.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.219"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:6.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "an3.72:6.2"
msgid "Na ceva nāma sadhammukkaṃsanā bhavissati, na ca paradhammāpasādanā."
msgstr ""
"There’s no acclaiming your own teaching or disrespecting someone else’s,"

msgctxt "an3.72:6.3"
msgid "Āyataneva dhammadesanā, attho ca vutto, attā ca anupanīto."
msgstr ""
"just teaching what’s relevant in that context. The goal is spoken of, but "
"the self is not involved."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.4"
msgid ""
"Tumhe, bhante ānanda, rāgassa pahānāya dhammaṃ desetha, dosassa … pe … "
"mohassa pahanāya dhammaṃ desetha."
msgstr "You, sir, teach Dhamma for giving up greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.5"
msgid "Tumhākaṃ, bhante ānanda, dhammo svākkhāto."
msgstr "Your teaching is well explained."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.6"
msgid ""
"Tumhe, bhante ānanda, rāgassa pahānāya paṭipannā, dosassa … pe … mohassa "
"pahānāya paṭipannā."
msgstr "You, sir, practice for giving up greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.7"
msgid "Tumhe, bhante, loke suppaṭipannā."
msgstr "You in the world are practicing well."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.8"
msgid ""
"Tumhākaṃ, bhante ānanda, rāgo pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato "
"anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo, tumhākaṃ doso pahīno … pe … tumhākaṃ "
"moho pahīno ucchinnamūlo tālāvatthukato anabhāvaṃkato āyatiṃ anuppādadhammo."
msgstr "You’ve given up greed, hate, and delusion."

msgctxt "an3.72:6.9"
msgid "Tumhe loke sukatā."
msgstr "You in the world have done well."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.72:7.1"
msgid "Abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "Excellent, sir! Excellent!"

msgctxt "an3.72:7.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, "
"mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya: ‘"
"cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ ayyena ānandena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Venerable Ānanda has made the teaching clear in "
"many ways."

msgctxt "an3.72:7.3"
msgid ""
"Esāhaṃ, bhante ānanda, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca "
"bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to the Buddha, to the teaching, and to the mendicant Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an3.72:7.4"
msgid "Upāsakaṃ maṃ ayyo ānando dhāretu, ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Venerable Ānanda remember me as a lay follower who "
"has gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.72:7.5"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
